    • Constructor Detail

      • EPSComms

        public EPSComms()
        Constructor.

      • EPSComms

        public EPSComms​(int errorCode,
                String translatedErrorMessage)
        Constructs a EPSComms with the given error code and translated error description. This is meant to be used in the POS client side when re-composing the EPSComm object. The POS side doesn't have the language translation files for EFTLink. Therefore we need this constructor so that the translated error description will be set and can be access by the POS or the REST API.
        Parameters:
        errorCode - the error code
        translatedErrorMessage - the translated error description

      • EPSComms

        public EPSComms​(String translatedErrorMessage)
        Constructs a EPSComms given the translated error description. This is meant to be used in the POS client side when re-composing the EPSComm object. The POS side doesn't have the language translation files for EFTLink. Therefore we need this constructor so that the translated error description will be set and can be access by the POS or the REST API.
        Parameters:
        translatedErrorMessage - the translated error description
